title: The number 3 and the letter E are inverse of the same shape
author: dcvlad

comments.content:
CYBERCORP looks like it's constructed from bits and pieces of Handel Gothic [http://www.identifont.com/find?font=Handel+Gothic&q=Go](http://web.archive.org/web/20150415194332/http:/www.identifont.com/find?font=Handel+Gothic&q=Go "http://www.identifont.com/find?font=Handel+Gothic&q=Go")  
It's possible that these letters have been developed into a techno style font. Might be worth going through fonts tagged techno, sci fi, future etc. to see if this is the case.  
Don

|CYBERCORP| probably began life as Ray Larabie’s NASA Medium (1997), which is now available as Nasalization:  
 [http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/typodermic/nasalization/](http://web.archive.org/web/20150415194332/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/typodermic/nasalization/ "http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/typodermic/nasalization/")

Yes, Nasalization is the closest for CYBERCORP. I had forgotten about it.  
Don
